ion integrated into the rooftop photovoltaic assembly. [Data: Entities (2399,2400); Relationships (3605)].\"},{\"summary\":\"Cable specification and responsibility scoping are centralized in the CABLE SCHEDULE, which lists cable types and includes responsibility scopes/remarks.\",\"explanation\":\"The CABLE SCHEDULE is described as a consolidated reference listing cable types, identifiers, routes, and remarks that clarify how each cable is applied within the project, and it includes responsibility scopes associated with the listed cables. This means the design package is intended to support traceability of both technical and accountability aspects of wiring. [Data: Entities (2404); Relationships (3910)].\\n\\nAt least one cable type used in the installation is explicitly shown as listed in the cable schedule: F-CV. [Data: Entities (2617,2404); Relationships (3910)].\\n\\nThe cable schedule also validates the electrical interconnection between key distribution points (3S DISTRIBUTION BOARD to SWITCHGEAR PANEL), implying that the schedule functions as the authoritative bridge between drawings/equipment and implemented wiring. [Data: Entities (2396,2626,2404); Relationships (3914)].\"},{\"summary\":\"Construction responsibilities appear deliberately divided between SOLAR POWER CONSTRUCTION COMPANY and ELECTRICAL CONSTRUCTION COMPANY across different technical domains.\",\"explanation\":\"SOLAR POWER CONSTRUCTION COMPANY is stated to be responsible for solar power-related construction scope, including installation and related works for solar modules, the 3S system, inverters, power lines, and associated cabling—covering integration of key PV components into the facility. [Data: Entities (2628); Relationships (3915)].\\n\\nThe relationships also indicate that SOLAR POWER CONSTRUCTION COMPANY’s scope includes the 3S SYSTEM, with remarks tying contractor responsibility to the 3S SYSTEM. This suggests that the solar contractor is accountable for the 3S-system-related implem